      javax.sound.midi.Track TrackFactory.addOnOtherChannel(Song song, javax.sound.midi.Track track, byte channel, boolean startAtZero)
      add a MidiPart (transformed to MidiEvents) to a track but on an other channel if afterwards something is added, it will start after the last event on the channel playing longest(if startAtZero is not toggled) always make sure you are not adding MidiEvents with ticks equal to already existing MidiEvents, as the result will sound horrible
      javax.sound.midi.Track TrackFactory.addToTrack(javax.sound.midi.Track track, Song song, boolean partsOnSameChannel)
      adds the information contained in the Song to the Track (on channel 1) in form of MidiEvents the added Song will be played after the already existing music is finished
      javax.sound.midi.Sequence SequenceGenerator.createSequence(Song song, boolean miditype0)
      builds a Sequence on basis of the given song
      if miditype0 == false every Part will be saved on a different track
      else every Part will be added on an other channel of the same track
      javax.sound.midi.Track TrackFactory.createTrack(javax.sound.midi.Sequence seq, Song song, boolean partsOnSameChannel)
      creates a new MidiTrack in which the given parts (in form of a Song) are represented
      void TrackFactory.createTracks(javax.sound.midi.Sequence seq, Song song)
      creates a track on the Sequence for every part in the song
      private void TrackFactory.SongIteration(Song song, javax.sound.midi.Track track, long counter)
